message.content:
cs.DC, cs.PL, cs.AR, cs.DS, cs.PF

Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper is about parallel programming and designing efficient schedulers for multicore processors. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also likely as the paper proposes a new dataflow composition construct to express partial dependencies in algorithms. 
- cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) is relevant as the paper discusses cache-oblivious algorithms and their performance on different levels of cache hierarchies. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is relevant as the paper redesigns several divide-and-conquer algorithms in the Nested Dataflow model. 
- cs.PF (Performance) is relevant as the paper provides theoretical guarantees on the efficiency of the proposed schedulers and algorithms.
